{"lemma":"طُوبَى","slug":"طُوبَى","root":"ط.#.ب","root_slug":"ط-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طُوبَى","root":"طيب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27244","n27414"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of أَطْيَب (ʔaṭyab)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blessedness, beatitude"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Beatitude (title of honor of a patriarch)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ṭūbā (tree in al-Janna)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"See the etymology of the corresponding lemma form.\n\nBorrowed from Aramaic טוּבַא / ܛܘܒܐ (ṭūḇā)."},"ipa":["/tˤuː.baː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27244","headword_ar":"طُوبَى","root":"Twb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tyb","text_ar":"طيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27414","headword_ar":"طُوبَى","root":"Tyb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolaY","text_ar":"فُعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~iybu","text_ar":"الطِّيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuyobaY","text_ar":"طُيْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Zj, S, O, Msb,) an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbN","text_ar":"طَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ksh and Bd in xiii. 28,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn."},{"kind":"text","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybN","text_ar":"طِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Seer, K: [in my MS copy of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tay~ib","text_ar":"طَيِّب"},{"kind":"text","text":", a manifest mistake:]) and fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToyabu","text_ar":"اَطْيَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISd, K:) and pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tay~ibapN","text_ar":"طَيِّبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) accord. to Kr, who says that there is no word like it except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsaY","text_ar":"كُوسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isapN","text_ar":"كَيِّسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuwqaY","text_ar":"ضُوقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Day~iqapN","text_ar":"ضَيِّقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but ISd says that, in his opinion,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY","text_ar":"طُوبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsaY","text_ar":"كُوسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuwqaY","text_ar":"ضُوقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"are fems. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToyabu","text_ar":"اَطْيَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyasu","text_ar":"اَكْيَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoyaqu","text_ar":"اَضْيَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolaY","text_ar":"فُعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not a pl. measure: Kr also adds that they did not say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybaY","text_ar":"طِيبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiysaY","text_ar":"كِيسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyqaY","text_ar":"ضِيقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA; [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuwqaY","text_ar":"ضُوقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dyq","text_ar":"ضيق"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) [but Sgh says that] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybaY","text_ar":"طِيبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY","text_ar":"طُوبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O:) Aboo-Hátim Sahl Ibn-Mohammad Es-Sijistánee relates that an Arab of the desert, reciting as a pupil to him, persisted in pronouncing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuyobaY","text_ar":"طُيْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY","text_ar":"طُوبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) it signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonaY","text_ar":"حُسْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good final,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ultimate, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and (some say, O, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good, good fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, Msb, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyrapN","text_ar":"خِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God's blessing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (K;) as some say: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eternal life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pleasant life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and (O, K) a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain tree in Paradise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) thus the Prophet is related to have said; and MF says that it is a proper name thereof, not admitting the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like is said in the M: (TA:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paradise"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Indian language; (O, K;) or, accord. to Sa'eed Ibn-Jubeyr, in the Abyssinian language: (O:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybaY","text_ar":"طِيبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) These different significations are assigned by different persons to this word in the phrase in the Kur [xiii. 28]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY lahumo","text_ar":"طُوبَى لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which seems to be best rendered as an announcement, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good final state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be to them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be their lot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb, TA:) Sb holds that it is an invocation of good, or a prayer, [as though"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qulo","text_ar":"قُلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. “ say thou ” were understood before it,] and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TwbY","text_ar":"طوبى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is virtually in the nom. case, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marofuwE","text_ar":"مَرْفُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is shown by the words immediately following"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHusonu maA=bK","text_ar":"وَحُسْنُ مَا=بٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but Th, who makes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TwbY","text_ar":"طوبى"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be an inf. n. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaY","text_ar":"رُجْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", says that one reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY lahumo waHusona maA=bK","text_ar":"طُوبَى لَهُمْ وَحُسْنَ مَا=بٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqoyFA lahu","text_ar":"سَقْيًا لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": MF, however, [supposing Th to have said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbFY","text_ar":"طُوبًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", though I think it indubitable that he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY","text_ar":"طُوبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and only meant that it was used as virtually, not literally, with tenween,] observes that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEFY","text_ar":"رُجْعًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with tenween, is not known to have been transmitted from any one of the leading authorities on the Arabic language. (TA.) Katádeh says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY lahumo","text_ar":"طُوبَى لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase of the Arabs; who say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY laka A_ino faEalota ka*aA","text_ar":"طُوبَى لَكَ اـِنْ فَعَلْتَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waka*aA","text_ar":"وَكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good final state"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thy lot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be to thee, if thou do such and such things"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY lil$~aA^omi","text_ar":"طُوبَى لِلشَّاْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betide Syria"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; in which case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TwbY","text_ar":"طوبى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolaY","text_ar":"فُعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~iybu","text_ar":"الطِّيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and does not mean “ Paradise, ” nor “ the tree. ” (L, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY laka","text_ar":"طُوبَى لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaAka","text_ar":"طُوبَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuwabyoka","text_ar":"طُوَبيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Yaakoob, S, O: [in one of my copies of the S"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuwbiyka","text_ar":"طُوبِيكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaAka","text_ar":"طُوبَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a barbarism: (O, K:) it is disallowed by the T, and by most of the grammarians: but Akh says that it is used by some of the Arabs; and Ibn-El-Moatezz uses it in the following verse:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"mar~ato binaA saHarFA TayorN faqulotu lahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        TuwbaAki yaA layotanaA A_iy~aAki TuwbaAki"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A flock of birds passed by us a little before daybreak, and I said to them, Good betide you: would that we were you: good betide you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: Esh-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1902},{"kind":"text","text":"Shiháb El-Khafájee says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is understood [before the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TwbAk","text_ar":"طوباك"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but MF has argued well against this assertion. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Zj","S","O","Msb","ISd","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B7%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%89/","headword_ar":"طوبى","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_24","lexicon_en":"Al-Tahānawī, Kashshāf Iṣṭilāḥāt al-Funūn wa-l-ʿUlūm (d. 1777 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كشّاف اصطلاحات الفنون والعلوم للتهانوي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=42378#42545f","body_html":"<span>طوبى:</span><br><span>[في الانكليزية] Tuba (Egyptian month)</span><br><span>[ في الفرنسية] Touba (mois egyptien)</span><br><span>اسم شهر في تقويم القبط القديم.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_40","lexicon_en":"Al-Suyūṭī, al-Muhadhdhib fī-mā Waqaʿa fi l-Qurʾān min al-Muʿarrab (d. 1505 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المهذب فيما وقع في القرآن من المعرب للسيوطي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=42378#9181bc","body_html":"<span>(طوبى) : قال ابن جرير: (حدثنا أبو كريب حدثنا يحيى بن يمان عن أشعب من جعفر عن سعيد بن جرير عن ابن عباس قال: طوبى اسم الجنة بلسان الحبشة) وقال: حدثنا ابن حميد حدثنا يعقوب القمى عن جعفر عن سعيد بن سحوج قال: طوبى اسم الجنة بالهندية.</span>"}]}}